class_name TransvoxelTransitionTables
extends RefCounted

## Transvoxel Algorithm transition-cell lookup tables.
##
## The data in this file is part of the author's implementation of the
## Transvoxel Algorithm and came from https://transvoxel.org/
## (Copyright 2009 by Eric Lengyel). Reproduced under the terms stated in
## that source — free use in implementations of the algorithm with credit.
##
## Tables sourced via Zylann/godot_voxel's transvoxel_tables.cpp (which
## re-credits Lengyel). See transvoxel.org for the canonical C++ originals.
##
## Layout summary (full encoding details in Lengyel's dissertation):
##
##   CELL_CLASS[case_code]
##     9-bit case code (one bit per high-res sample 0..8) → 8-bit value.
##     Low 7 bits  : equivalence-class index in CELL_GEOM/CELL_INDICES (0..55).
##     High bit    : if set, reverse triangle winding (case is the inverse).
##
##   CELL_GEOM[class]
##     High nibble : vertex count (number of edge-crossings in the cell).
##     Low nibble  : triangle count.
##
##   CELL_INDICES[class]
##     Flat list of vertex indices (each 0..vertex_count-1), triangle_count*3
##     entries total. Same order as Lengyel's tables.
##
##   CORNER_DATA[corner_index]                       (corner_index 0..12)
##     Encoded as ((reuse_direction & 0xf) << 4) | (slot & 0xf). Used for
##     vertex caching across face cells — we currently re-emit every vertex
##     instead of sharing, so this table is parked here for future use.
##
##   VERTEX_DATA[case_code * 12 + i]                 (i in 0..vertex_count-1)
##     16-bit per edge crossing:
##       bits 0..3  : transition-cell corner A index (0..12)
##       bits 4..7  : transition-cell corner B index (0..12)
##       bits 8..11 : reuse slot index               (for sharing — unused here)
##       bits 12..15: reuse direction bits           (for sharing — unused here)
##
## Transition-cell corner layout (per Lengyel):
##
##   high-res face (3x3 = 9 samples)        low-res face (2x2 = 4 samples)
##     6---7---8                              B-------C
##     |   |   |                              |       |
##     3---4---5                              |       |
##     |   |   |                              |       |
##     0---1---2                              9-------A
##
## Half-res samples 9..12 reuse the values of fine corners 0,2,6,8 — the
## low-res face is conceptually the coarser neighbour's view of the boundary
## face, sampled with twice the spacing, which our implementation gets for
## free by reading the same corner samples.


